nge its major subsidiaries are celulose do caima paper industry and celbi paper industry altris f ramada subsidiary which produced steel and storage systems such as cold rolled steel sheets and strips machinery tools and other related products was spun off on the stock exchange in  altri was itself born from a spinout of the industrial assets of the cofina group in march  referencesedit  a b c annual report  altri retrieved  july    altri says new shares from steel unit spinoff to start trading early july afx news forbes  june  retrieved  november    lisbon shares sharply higher as bcp rockets  pct after it loses bcr deal afx news forbes  december  retrieved  november   external linksedit official website v t e psi companies of portugal altri banco comercial português banco português de investimento banif ctt correios de portugal energias de portugal edp renováveis galp energia impresa jerónimo martins motaengil nos portucel soporcel pharol redes energéticas nacionais semapa sonae teixeira duarte this european corporation or company article is a stub you can help wikipedia by expanding it v t e this portugalrelated article is a stub you can help wikipedia by expanding it v t e retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlealtrioldid categories conglomerate companies of portugalcompanies based in portocompanies established in pulp and paper companies of portugaleuropean company stubsportugal stubshidden categories pages using deprecated image syntaxall stub articlesuse dmy dates from june  navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurrent eventsrandom articledonate to wikipediawikipedia store interaction helpabout wikipediacommunity portalrecent changescontact page tools what links hererelated changesupload filespecial pagespermanent linkpage informationwikidata itemcite this page printexport create a bookdown